----- Begin Included Message -----

Per, Robert, CORE (info)

As requested by Per, I have sorted the draft master skills list into
"similar type" groups, and the *provisional* result is -

Category      Encompassing
------------------------------------------------
Artisan       Mechanical/trade based skills
Combat        Conflict resolution skills 
Creative      Skills associated with the "arts" 
General       Common/unrestricted skills
Lore          Learned/knowledge skills
Manipulative  Skills used to confer an advantage
Survival      Living/hunting/adventuring type skills  
Willforce     Mind/chi based skills   

In the following sub-tables, an "xx" means that this skill will not be
written up for play-testing (we may decided to add more "xx"s as we go along). 

NB: the skills committee has agreed that it will not get bogged down
discussing Tr rate, hurdle, Default TD and Talent numbers, anybody can
change anything they don't like without discussion since for playtesting
purposes one rating/number is as good as another. The whole lot will
probably get changed after playtesting anyway so why bother talking about it
now? :) Let's keep this thing moving - look ahead!

2NB: Re combat skills. For playtesting purposes (and unless anybody screams)
we propose going with four (or more) or so skills -

Basic weapon (club, sword, ax, whatever)
Power weapon (2 handed anything, polearm)
Shield
Ranged weapon (anything from a dagger to siege x-bow)
Anything important that I've forgotten or that is not listed here but we
think should go into playtesting.
 
All the fancy stuff (e.g., two weapons, unarmed combat, articulated weapons,
thrown weapons, martial arts, whips, nets etc.) can be developed later, once
we know how well *basic* combat works, as a result of playtesting. Let's not
get bogged down in too much detail - keep things moving!

